Source:  Austral English
Author:  MORRIS
Vol / Page:  471
Edition:
Quote:  Titipounamu, n. (<i>spelt also </i>Tititipunamu), n. <i>Maori name for the bird Acanthidositta chloris,</i> Sparm., the <i>Rifleman</i> (q.v.). It has many other Maori names.
Notes:

Date:  0/0/1947
Source:  Native Animals of NZ
Author:  POWELL
Vol / Page:  86
Edition:
Quote:  RIFLEMAN (<i>Acanthisitta chloris</i>). This is a wren and our smallest bird, being only three inches in total length. There are two forms, typical chloris from the South Island and <i>A. chloris granti,</i> the North Island rifleman....The Maori name is Titi-pounamu.
Notes:

Date:  5/2/1995
Source:  NZ Tablet
Author:
Vol / Page:  7
Edition:
Quote:  It's a titipounamu, and you often find him in the ti-tree scrub... It is the rifleman, very shy, and a friend of the scrub-cutter.
